25c.title: Some men just want to watch the world learn
25c.text:
[@2] has just made the first [ LINK public announcement] about Arbital. We are showcasing [1zq his explanation of the Bayes' Theorem]. Check it out and let us know what you think. Arbital as it stands right now is fully geared to [1sm help the world learn].

Here are some of the things we've been working on:

**Dynamically generated path**: [1rt obviously]!

**Requisites page**: You can now [https://arbital.com/requisites see and change] all the requisites you've ever interacted with.

**Page contributors**: Pages now show a list of people who have contributed.

**Instant comments**: When you create comments, they now instantly appear on the page without a reload.

**Editor only comments**: When writing a new comment, you can choose to make it visible only to the editors of the page. Others can still see them if they choose to, but they are hidden by default.

**Bug fixes and UI improvements**: too many to list here, but big thanks to everyone who have submitted a bug report!

## Community

Should out to [@1yq] for taking full advantage of our [1c2 community input] page.

### Featured page

As part of our community section, we'll start picking a recently created page that we want to highlight. Obviously, this time around it's [1zq]. If you haven't looked at it yet, do so now. That page shows off what Arbital is capable of.

## Looking forward

### Announcement postmortem

Expect a pretty quick followup on how the announcement went. At that point we'll also have more to say about next features and growth areas.

### Public launch

This is not our official launch per-se. Like we mentioned in the previous blog post, that will come towards the end of April. At that time we'll open up the platform to all groups, communities, and individuals for mostly any kind of content. We will have the necessary features and adjustments in place to make sure that the communities don't interfere with each other, but can still collaborate.

*Subscribe to [16q Arbital's blog] to receive updates when there are new posts.*
